        "email": "elena.gryaznova@hpe.com",
        "username": "elena"
      },
      "date": "2018-10-11 19:08:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHello James.\nSorry for the question, but why Maloo runs all sanity if envdefinitions=ONLY=56ba is set?\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "8bb8e233aca73a892f1313c00f4fdbb984c27a2e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2018-10-11 20:25:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nYes, this is a little confusing. When you use the \"trivial\" test parameter, this means only run one test group which is review-ldiskfs. If you have any other test parameters, then an additional, custom, test group will be run. \n\nIf you look at the results, you have a review-ldiskfs and a custom test session. For this patch, you could just use the \"trivial\" test parameter and leave off the testlist=sanity because sanity is part of review-ldiskfs. \n\nAlso, sanity test 77k was added back to the ALWAYS_EXCEPT list. So, a rebase of this patch should stop that failure.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
